Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim @Brussels Sprouts{8%oz}; halve or quarter lengthwise depending on size. Peel and dice @Sweet Potatoes{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and core @Apple{1}; thinly slice one half (whole apple for 4 servings). Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Halve @Ciabatta Bread{1} lengthwise. Remove and discard any large stems from @Kale{4%oz}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss Brussels sprouts and sweet potato with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%tsp}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread out across a #baking sheet{}.

Roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Let cool at least ~{5%minutes}.

Once veggies are almost done, place @Butter{2%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in garlic to taste, then brush onto cut sides of ciabatta. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place ciabatta cut sides up on one side of a second baking sheet.

Lightly oil opposite side of sheet with ciabatta; sprinkle @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup} into two 3-inch-wide circles (four circles for 4 servings) on sheet.

Bake on middle rack until ciabatta is toasted and frico is golden brown and crisp, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> Check often to make sure the cheese doesn't burn.

Let frico cool on sheet until hardened, then carefully transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

While ciabatta toasts, place kale in bowl used for veggies; season lightly with @salt{} and a drizzle of oil. Massage kale until leaves soften, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add sliced apple, @Dried Cranberries{1.16%oz}, and ¾ of the roasted veggies to bowl with kale. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add @Honey Dijon Dressing{4.5%oz} to taste and toss to combine.

Halve garlic bread on a diagonal. Break up frico into bite-size pieces.

Divide salad between #plates{} or #shallow bowls{}. Garnish with remaining roasted veggies and frico. Serve with garlic bread on the side.